rtedly made a whopping $200 million in 2012.","dropCap":false},"innerBlocks":[]},{"clientId":"b9a5cc67-23b0-48ad-ac35-1405e93d46ce","name":"core/paragraph","attributes":{"content":"In 2011, \u003cem\u003eSkylanders: Spyro’s Adventure\u003c/em\u003e brought video games into the physical world. The game required players to place plastic toy figures (sold separately) onto an accessory, which reads the toys’ NFC tags to bring the characters into the game. The next few years would see several sequels and other toy-video game hybrids, such as \u003cem\u003eDisney Infinity\u003c/em\u003e, which features Disney characters.","dropCap":false},"innerBlocks":[]},{"clientId":"fc650092-5412-4dbb-8b52-81490b5e0fd4","name":"core/paragraph","attributes":{"content":"The 8th generation of video games began with the release of Nintendo’s Wii U in 2012, followed by the Playstation 4 and Xbox One in 2013. Despite featuring a touch screen remote control that allowed off-TV gaming and being able to play Wii games, the Wii U was a commercial failure—the opposite of its competition—and was discontinued in 2017.","dropCap":false},"innerBlocks":[]},{"clientId":"3741f240-814e-4803-91cd-84c5a7c662a5","name":"core/paragraph","attributes":{"content":"In early 2017, Nintendo released its Wii U successor, the Nintendo Switch, the only system to allow both television-based and handheld gaming. Microsoft released its 4K-ready console, the Xbox One X, in late 2017, and followed up in 2020 with the Xbox Series X and Series S. In 2020, Sony released the Playstation 5, a successor to\u0026nbsp;Playstation 4.\u0026nbsp;","dropCap":false},"innerBlocks":[]},{"clientId":"8490a773-69ff-4df9-a1b6-215a76afa6da","name":"core/paragraph","attributes":{"content":"With their new revamped consoles, both Sony and Microsoft currently have their sights set on virtual reality gaming, a technology that has the potential to change the way players experience video games.","dropCap":false},"innerBlocks":[]},{"clientId":"e98ee