ga-and-nintendo-16-bit-console-war\"\u003ePrima Games\u003c/a\u003e.\u003cbr /\u003eAngry Birds Maker Rovio Reports $200 Million In Revenue, $71 Million In Profit For 2012. \u003ca href=\"http://www.businessinsider.com/angry-birds-made-200-million-in-2012-2013-4\"\u003eBusiness Insider\u003c/a\u003e.\u003cbr /\u003eHere’s who won each console war. \u003ca href=\"https://venturebeat.com/2014/08/20/heres-who-won-each-console-war/\"\u003eVenturebeat\u003c/a\u003e.\u003cbr /\u003eThe History Of Gaming: An Evolving Community. \u003ca href=\"https://techcrunch.com/2015/10/31/the-history-of-gaming-an-evolving-community/\"\u003eTechCrunch\u003c/a\u003e.\u003cbr /\u003eThe History of Video Game Consoles. \u003ca href=\"https://techcrunch.com/2015/10/31/the-history-of-gaming-an-evolving-community/\"\u003eTIME\u003c/a\u003e.","dropCap":false},"innerBlocks":[]}]},"excerpt":{"rendered":"The Early Days Though video games are found today in homes worldwide, they actually got their start in the research labs of scientists. In 1952, for instance, British professor A.S. Douglas created OXO, also known as noughts and crosses or a tic-tac-toe, as part of his doctoral dissertation at the University of Cambridge. And in […]","protected":false},"featured_media":8553,"menu_order":0,"template":"","meta":{"video_platform_id":"","video_duration":0,"video_content_rating":"","video_disable_autoplay":false,"subhead":"","exclude_from_rss":false,"distribute_scheduled_post":[],"curated_related_posts":"","disable_related_posts":""},"tags":[],"article_type":[],"story_byline":[406],"attribute":[6],"story_category":[50],"article_type_meta":"","tags_meta":"","disable_interrupter":"","primary_term":null,"video_thumbnail":false,"hide_on_google_news":false,"yoast_head_json":{"title":"Video Game History - Timeline \u0026 Facts","description":"Though video games are found today in homes worldwide, they actually got their start in the research labs of scientists early 1950s. Academics designed simple games, l